{
  "stem": "10272.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the rabbi said, his purpose is actually to fight communism.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we Jews, we should be neutral, at least, because what can we lose if these two two large powers, Germany and Russia, will fight each other?",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So these two nations can kill each other, and we should stay neutral, not to be on this side against Germany or with Russia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because we don't have nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We might lose.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Russia is actually against the Jews because they're atheist, against God.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many Jews who believe in Russia, they became also atheist.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they start to be assimilated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we are losing Jews, actually, Jews from our nation, our people, without the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Only because they became assimilated Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This is also a type of a holocaust, he says.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He tried to calm us down and explain to us we should not be alarmed because of the situation, of the whole situation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the other thing was, that he was trying to explain to us, the rabbi-- I told you, I said the assimilation thing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when we got home with my father, on my way home-- it took us about half an hour to get home from the synagogue to our home-- I was with him to hear this sermon of the rabbi, and I already at that time knew from our teacher in high school, I mean in the junior high, that Hitler wants to invade Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the teacher told us that Hitler is putting people, Jewish people or people who disagree with his policy, into concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He showed us a picture about Dachau.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For the first time in my life I heard the name Dachau.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know there are concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he explained us exactly what a concentration camp means.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
